Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.00,0:00:05.51,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Hello it's Scott Manley here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.00,0:00:05.51,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你好 我是斯科特-曼利
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.83,0:00:08.93,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Thanks to 20 years of continuous occupation of space
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.83,0:00:08.93,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,由于20年来对太空的持续占领
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.98,0:00:12.96,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,we have a wealth of photographs and videos from low earth orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.98,0:00:12.96,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我们拥有大量来自低地球轨道的照片和视频
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.96,0:00:15.04,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And they are wonderful things to watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.96,0:00:15.04,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它们是值得观看的美妙事物
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.36,0:00:20.40,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Sometimes they show amazing things like this Soyuz launching towards the ISS
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.36,0:00:20.40,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,有时 它们展示了令人惊奇的事情 比如这个联盟号向国际空间站发射的照片
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.55,0:00:26.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but even the random everyday views from low earth orbit are compelling and hypnotic.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.55,0:00:26.36,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但即使是来自低地球轨道的随机的日常景观也是令人信服和催眠的
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.71,0:00:31.09,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,They show the world moving slowly below the observer, land and sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.71,0:00:31.09,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它们显示了世界在观察者下方缓慢移动 陆地和海洋
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.14,0:00:35.01,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Sometimes cities and of course clouds hanging in the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.14,0:00:35.01,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,有时还有城市 当然还有悬挂在大气层中的云彩
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.66,0:00:41.35,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Looking to the edge of the globe you can see the thin atmosphere extending up towards space.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.66,0:00:41.35,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,向地球的边缘看去 你可以看到稀薄的大气层向太空延伸
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.66,0:00:43.52,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And it's always humbling to realize that
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.66,0:00:43.52,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,当你意识到以下情况时 你会感到很惭愧
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.52,0:00:45.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,every human that's ever lived
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.52,0:00:45.28,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,每一个曾经生活过的人类
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.49,0:00:50.89,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,has done so in this thin skin of air that clings to the surface of the earth by gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.49,0:00:50.89,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,都是在这层薄薄的空气中完成的 而这层空气在重力的作用下紧贴着地球表面
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.85,0:00:55.25,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,The blue fades into black as the air gets thinner
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.85,0:00:55.25,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,随着空气越来越稀薄 蓝色渐渐变成黑色
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.36,0:01:01.50,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but then something else appears a thin yellowish layer separate from the lower atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.36,0:01:01.50,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但随后出现了其他东西 一个从低层大气中分离出来的淡黄色薄层
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.68,0:01:04.63,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And this stands out against the blackness of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.68,0:01:04.63,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而这在黑色的太空中显得尤为突出
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.00,0:01:08.39,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,You might have seen this before and wondered what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.00,0:01:08.39,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你可能以前见过这个 想知道它是什么
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.12,0:01:11.10,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,This is the sodium layer.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.12,0:01:11.10,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这就是钠层
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.43,0:01:16.24,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It's between 80 and 105 kilometers up depending upon atmospheric conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.43,0:01:16.24,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它在80至105公里的高度 取决于大气条件
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.29,0:01:18.02,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and it's only a few kilometers thick.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.29,0:01:18.02,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而且它只有几公里厚
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.65,0:01:23.02,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,This is a region of the atmosphere where sodium atoms are being excited
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.65,0:01:23.02,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这是大气层中的一个区域 钠原子被激发出来
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.11,0:01:29.78,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and emitting light in the familiar yellow color with a wavelength of about 589 nanometers.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.11,0:01:29.78,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,并发射出熟悉的黄色光 波长约为589纳米
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.57,0:01:34.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,The sodium comes from meteors burning up in the upper atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.57,0:01:34.28,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,钠来自于在大气层上部燃烧的流星
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.63,0:01:39.44,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,As they hit the atmosphere the kinetic energy is converted into thermal energy
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.63,0:01:39.44,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,当它们撞击大气层时 动能被转化为热能
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.52,0:01:42.18,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and this converts their minerals into a plasma
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.52,0:01:42.18,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,并将其矿物转化为等离子体
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.41,0:01:48.03,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,which of course we see as a trail of light on the ground as a shooting star which fades rapidly.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.41,0:01:48.03,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,当然 我们在地面上看到的是流星的光迹 它迅速消失
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.60,0:01:51.65,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But those liberated atoms remain afterwards
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.60,0:01:51.65,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但是那些被解放的原子后来仍然存在
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.94,0:01:53.97,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and they stay there for a long time
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.94,0:01:53.97,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它们在那里停留了很长时间
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.15,0:01:58.60,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,hanging out in the mesosphere perhaps percolating downwards towards the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.15,0:01:58.60,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,悬挂在中间层 也许会向下渗透到表面
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.36,0:02:05.83,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So this visible sodium layer is a lot thinner than the distribution of sodium atoms in the atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.36,0:02:05.83,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以这个可见的钠层比大气中的钠原子分布要薄得多
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.18,0:02:11.07,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,because the transition line that we see only comes from neutral atomic sodium.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.18,0:02:11.07,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因为我们看到的过渡线只来自中性原子钠
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.28,0:02:16.62,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,As we go higher in the atmosphere the sodium atoms are more commonly found as ions
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.28,0:02:16.62,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,当我们在大气层中的位置越高 钠原子就越多地以离子形式存在
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.91,0:02:22.48,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and lower in the atmosphere the atoms are more formal or more commonly found in their molecular state
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.91,0:02:22.48,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而在大气层的低处 原子更正式或更普遍地以分子状态出现
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.52,0:02:28.84,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and so we see this yellow glowing layer standing out away from the surface of the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.52,0:02:28.84,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以我们看到这个黄色的发光层远离地球的表面
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.27,0:02:33.54,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and as it happens this altitude is very close to that of the Karman line
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.27,0:02:33.54,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,碰巧这个高度非常接近卡曼线的高度
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.91,0:02:38.05,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,so it's almost like a visual reference for where space begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.91,0:02:38.05,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以它几乎是空间开始的一个视觉参考
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.80,0:02:42.16,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Now the meteors are arriving at earth don't just bring in sodium.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.80,0:02:42.16,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,现在 到达地球的流星不只是带来了钠
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.16,0:02:43.76,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,They have many other minerals.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.16,0:02:43.76,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它们还有许多其他矿物
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.76,0:02:46.83,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And all of these also get deposited in the atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.76,0:02:46.83,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而所有这些也都沉积在大气中
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.31,0:02:50.02,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and over time scientists have managed to identify
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.31,0:02:50.02,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而且随着时间的推移 科学家们已经设法确定
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.06,0:02:54.70,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,the existence of other similar layers dominated by different elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.06,0:02:54.70,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,其他由不同元素主导的类似层的存在
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.11,0:02:57.75,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,We've seen iron potassium and calcium.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.11,0:02:57.75,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我们已经看到铁、钾和钙
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.23,0:03:00.64,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But none of these are as strong as the sodium.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.23,0:03:00.64,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但这些都没有钠那么强
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.64,0:03:07.20,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Because the sodium is extremely efficient at converting the excitation energy into light that we can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.64,0:03:07.20,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因为钠在将激发的能量转化为我们可以看到的光方面非常有效
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.20,0:03:10.05,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,That's why we have low pressure sodium lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.20,0:03:10.05,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这就是为什么我们有低压钠灯
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.72,0:03:16.18,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So the sodium layer was first discovered from the ground using spectroscopy back in 1929
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.72,0:03:16.18,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因此 钠层是在1929年首次从地面用光谱学发现的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.40,0:03:21.65,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and since then it's been used by scientists as a way to probe atmospheric conditions in the mesosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.40,0:03:21.65,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,从那时起 科学家们就用它来探测中间层的大气状况
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.84,0:03:26.81,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,which is actually our region in the atmosphere which is really hard to investigate directly
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.84,0:03:26.81,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这实际上是我们在大气层中很难直接调查的区域
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.04,0:03:30.77,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,since it's too high for balloons and too low for spacecraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.04,0:03:30.77,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因为它对气球来说太高 对航天器来说太低
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.68,0:03:36.71,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Now from the ground you can use lasers to excite the atomic sodium in that region
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.68,0:03:36.71,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,现在从地面上 你可以使用激光来激发该区域的原子钠
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.87,0:03:40.11,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and then it re-emits the light which you can observe back on the ground
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.87,0:03:40.11,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,然后它重新发出光 你可以在地面上观察它
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.31,0:03:44.26,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and from that you can measure the motion of the atmosphere or the temperature.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.31,0:03:44.26,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,从中你可以测量大气的运动或温度
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.79,0:03:49.94,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,The temperature of the air depends or changes the shape of the emission lines that we see
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.79,0:03:49.94,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,空气的温度取决于或改变我们看到的发射线的形状
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.26,0:03:53.46,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and the doppler shift can of course change the wavelength that we see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.26,0:03:53.46,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而多普勒位移当然会改变我们看到的波长
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.08,0:03:58.24,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,There's one facility that i want to talk about that does a science like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.08,0:03:58.24,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我想说的是 有一个设施做这样的科学
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.26,0:04:02.70,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It's called the Purple Crow Lidar Facility in Ontario, Canada.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.26,0:04:02.70,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它被称为加拿大安大略省的紫乌鸦激光雷达设施
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.95,0:04:09.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And it's notable because the primary mirror on the collector system is a rotating mercury mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.95,0:04:09.28,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它值得注意的是 收集器系统的主镜是一个旋转的水银镜
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.42,0:04:13.26,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,That's a mirror that's essentially a 9 feet wide 2.65 meters.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.42,0:04:13.26,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,那是一个基本上是9英尺宽2.65米的镜子
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.52,0:04:18.79,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It's a tub of mercury and it's rotating at about 10 RPM
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.52,0:04:18.79,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它是一盆水银 以大约10转/分钟的速度旋转
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.79,0:04:24.92,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,which means that it takes up a natural curvature which will focus the light on the detector system.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.79,0:04:24.92,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这意味着它有一个自然的弧度 这将使光线集中在检测器系统上
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.28,0:04:27.84,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And the only way they can make this work by the way is
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.28,0:04:27.84,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,顺便说一下 他们能够使这个工作的唯一方法是
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.84,0:04:29.84,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,because it's only pointing straight up
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.84,0:04:29.84,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因为它只是直接指向上方
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.88,0:04:33.70,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,if the mirror had to turn then it would no longer be able to work like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.88,0:04:33.70,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,如果镜子必须转动 那么它将不再能够像这样工作
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.26,0:04:38.86,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But one of the coolest things that can be done with this sodium layer is that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.26,0:04:38.86,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但是用这个钠层可以做的最酷的事情之一就是
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.90,0:04:45.61,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,it can be exploited by telescopes to help them see more detail in the sky than would normally be possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.90,0:04:45.61,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它可以被望远镜所利用 以帮助他们看到比通常情况下更多的天空细节
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.31,0:04:50.12,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So as you probably know the resolving power of a telescope on the ground
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.31,0:04:50.12,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以 正如你可能知道的 地面上的望远镜的分辨能力
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.28,0:04:52.74,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,is limited by the turbulence of the atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.28,0:04:52.74,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,受限于大气层的湍流
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.94,0:04:55.98,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,which refracts the light from astronomical objects
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.94,0:04:55.98,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它使来自天文物体的光线发生折射
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.29,0:04:58.80,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and it's an effect that we can see with our naked eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.29,0:04:58.80,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这是一个我们可以用肉眼看到的效果
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.84,0:05:01.81,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It's what makes the stars twinkle in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.84,0:05:01.81,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这就是使星星在天空中闪烁的原因
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.63,0:05:05.40,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So telescopes can have adaptive optics.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.63,0:05:05.40,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因此 望远镜可以有自适应光学系统
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.46,0:05:11.79,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,This means the mirror is able to flex and change its shape in response to atmospheric distortion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.46,0:05:11.79,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这意味着镜子能够弯曲并改变其形状以应对大气的扭曲
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.16,0:05:15.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And so that it can actually undo the atmospheric distortion
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.16,0:05:15.36,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这样 它实际上可以消除大气变形
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.36,0:05:20.01,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and ultimately produce a much clearer image than would not otherwise be allowed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.36,0:05:20.01,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,并最终产生一个比其他方式不允许的更清晰的图像
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.61,0:05:24.08,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But to do this they need to know how the atmosphere is distorting the light
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.61,0:05:24.08,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但要做到这一点 他们需要知道大气层是如何扭曲光线的
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.08,0:05:28.66,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,so they take a reference star which you can assume to be a perfect point source
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.08,0:05:28.66,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以他们采取了一个参考星 你可以假设它是一个完美的点光源
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.02,0:05:31.96,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and then you measure that with a real-time camera
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.02,0:05:31.96,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,然后你用实时摄像机测量它
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.08,0:05:35.60,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,taking hundreds of frames per second measuring the distortion
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.08,0:05:35.60,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,每秒拍摄几百帧 测量扭曲情况
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.60,0:05:38.88,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and then feeding that back into the optic system
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.60,0:05:38.88,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,然后将其反馈给光学系统
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.95,0:05:41.33,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,so that it can undo the refraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.95,0:05:41.33,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这样它就可以消除折射了
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.74,0:05:44.86,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And it needs to be able to measure the star hundreds of times per second.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.74,0:05:44.86,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它需要能够每秒测量数百次的恒星
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.44,0:05:48.85,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,The problem then is that the star has to be bright enough
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.44,0:05:48.85,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,那么问题来了 恒星必须有足够的亮度
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.25,0:05:52.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,so they can take the image fast enough and get enough detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.25,0:05:52.28,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,以便他们能以足够快的速度拍摄图像并获得足够的细节
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.88,0:05:58.00,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And not all astronomical targets will have a bright star close enough to the target
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.88,0:05:58.00,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而不是所有的天文目标都有一颗足够接近目标的亮星
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.72,0:06:04.66,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,so instead the sodium layer can be used to generate an artificial reference star.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.72,0:06:04.66,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以钠层可以用来产生一个人工参考星
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.85,0:06:12.23,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,What you do is you have a laser which is tuned to excite the 589 nanometer sodium emission lines
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.85,0:06:12.23,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你所做的是你有一个激光器 它被调谐到激发589纳米的钠发射线上
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.56,0:06:14.86,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and you fire that up alongside the telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.56,0:06:14.86,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,然后你在望远镜旁边发射它
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.90,0:06:20.14,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and in the sodium layer it's generating light which is it essentially looks like a star.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.90,0:06:20.14,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,在钠层中 它产生的光从本质上看就像一颗星
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.69,0:06:23.90,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Technically it's a line through the atmosphere if you look at it from the side
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.69,0:06:23.90,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,从技术上讲 如果你从侧面看 它是一条穿过大气的线
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.94,0:06:26.14,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but since the laser is placed next to the telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.94,0:06:26.14,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但由于激光器被放置在望远镜的旁边
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.46,0:06:30.18,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,it appears to be sufficiently point-like to act as a reference star
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.46,0:06:30.18,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它看起来足够像一个点 可以作为一个参考星
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.51,0:06:34.54,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and deliver image details that would normally be twinkled to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.51,0:06:34.54,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,并提供通常会被闪烁死的图像细节
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.19,0:06:37.89,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,I'm Scott Manley. Fly safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.19,0:06:37.89,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我是斯科特-曼利 飞行安全
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.16,0:06:56.96,1080P-sgbd-4s,,0,0,0,,[Music]
